  "why": "The paper goes beyond simply reporting attack success and failure rates by investigating why token-level, gradient-guided attacks (GCG) fail under common defenses and transfer poorly. Through experiments with perplexity-based defense, paraphrasing defenses, transferability tests, and ablations, the authors trace these failures to underlying model vulnerabilities: reliance on non-semantic, spurious token artifacts that are easily flagged by perplexity detectors and overfitting to white-box gradient information. This diagnostic analysis links observed failure patterns to spurious features and overfitting—key vulnerabilities that can guide future defenses.",
